annéidigh</i>’ (from <i>ceann</i> ‘head’ + <i>éidigh</i> ‘ugly’); or from the Scottish Gaelic <b>Mac Cinnèidigh</b>, consisting of <i>mac</i> ‘son’ with an equivalent name. Compare   Canaday  ,   Cannady  ,   Cannedy  ,   Kannady  , and   Kenedy  .","History: Kennedy ancestral lands are found both in Ireland and in Scotland, where the family's medieval ancestral seat is sited on the Ayrshire coast, facing the Irish Sea. — The great-grandparents of President John Fitzgerald Kennedy (1917–63) came to North America as immigrants from Ireland in the 1840s. His paternal great-grandparents were Patrick Kennedy (1823–58), born in Dunganstown, County Wexford, Ireland, and Bridget Murphy, who was born probably in Owenduff, County Wexford, Ireland <i>c.</i> 1827; they came to Boston, MA, in 1849. His maternal great-grandparents were Thomas Fitzgerald (1823–85), who was born in Bruff, County Limerick, Ireland, and Rose Anna Cox, who was born probably in Tomregan or Kinawley, County Cavan, Ireland, <i>c.</i> 1835; they came to Boston, MA, in 1857. — An early Scottish Kennedy forebear of a quite different family was British colonial official Archibald Kennedy (1685–1763), the son of Alexander Kennedy of Craigoch, who emigrated to NY <i>c.</i> 1710."],"variants":[{"name":"Canada","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canaday   and   Canida  .","Spanish (<b>Cañada</b>): topographic name from <i>cañada</i> ‘glen, valley’."]},{"name":"Cannady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canady  ,   Cannaday  , and   Kannady  ."]},{"name":"Cannaday","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canaday  ."]},{"name":"Canedy","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Cannedy  ."]},{"name":"Cannedy","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canedy  ."]},{"name":"Canaday","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canada   and   Cannaday  ."]},{"name":"Canady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canada  ,   Canaday  , and   Kanady  ."]},{"name":"Canida","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  ."]},{"name":"Kanady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canady  ."]},{"name":"Kannady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Cannady   and   Kanady  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs John Kennedy was born about 1469, in Scotland. She had at least 1 son with John Kennedy 4th of Blairquhan."},"et":{"about 1469–":"umbes 1469–Surnud","1469–1515":"1469–1515","1484–1522":"1484–1522","1469–Female":"1469–Surnud","1469":"1469","1522":"1522","before 1484":"enne 1484","about 1469":"umbes 1469","1484":"1484","1515":"1515","Blairquhan, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Blairquhan, Ayrshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1469–":"noin 1469–Kuollut","1469–1515":"1469–1515","1484–1522":"1484–1522","1469–Female":"1469–Kuollut","1469":"1469","1522":"1522","before 1484":"ennen vuotta 1484","about 1469":"noin 1469","1484":"1484","1515":"1515","Blairquhan, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Blairquhan, Ayrshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1469–":"environ 1469–Décédée","1469–1515":"1469–1515","1484–1522":"1484–1522","1469–Female":"1469–Décédée","1469":"1469","1522":"1522","before 1484":"avant 1484","about 1469":"environ 1469","1484":"1484","1515":"1515","Blairquhan, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Blairquhan, Ayrshire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","lifeSummary":"Mrs John Kennedy est née environ 1469, à Écosse. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec John Kennedy 4th of Blairquhan."},"de":{"about 1469–":"um 1469–Verstorben","1469–1515":"1469–1515","1484–1522":"1484–1522","1469–Female":"1469–Verstorben","1469":"1469","1522":"1522","before 1484":"vor 1484","about 1469":"um 1469","14